{
  "stem": "3022.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one-- and one of our-- as we were marching down towards going back west, one time we stopped by the roadside in order to rest.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the convoy of Polish [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "PWs ?] escorted by Germans, prisoners passed by.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the Poles pointed us out to the Germans, saying [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] Juden, Juden.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the officer on the horse came over to us and asked us, [GERMAN] Juden?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now there's a law in Jewish religion that forbids you to deny that you are a Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as well you may-- it was well known that all laws are suspended in, in, in, in Jewish tradition when it comes to save your life, except for three laws.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Only in three instances, you know, the pikuach nefesh law does not apply-- the law of saving your life.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's the instance of, of idolatry, of, of, licentious behavior, and of murder.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In other words, you could not save your life and give somebody else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because the law says, how do you know that your blood is better than somebody else?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it is forbidden by that law to deny that you are a Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You are supposed to suffer martyrdom before you deny that you are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So when the officer asked us, [GERMAN] Juden?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Are you Jews?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Automatically, we said, yes, we are Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he picked us up, and we had to run in front of the horse for several kilometers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He tried to exhaust us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then he was called to some other detail, and we ran away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was next encounter that we had with the behavior of the Polish citizenry.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[SIGHS] We arrived about two weeks later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We came back to Cracow.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
